# Build & Ship After Every Edit (MANDATORY)

After every code change, run ALL of the following steps in order:

## 1. Android Builds
```bash
cd flutter-app

# Prod APK
flutter build apk --release --flavor prod --dart-define=INSTAGOLD_FLAVOR=prod
cp build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-prod-release.apk ../InstaGold.apk

# Prod AAB
flutter build appbundle --release --flavor prod --dart-define=INSTAGOLD_FLAVOR=prod
cp build/app/outputs/bundle/prodRelease/app-prod-release.aab ../InstaGold.aab

# Install on Android emulator
adb install -r ../InstaGold.apk
adb shell monkey -p com.ibrahym.goldfamily -c android.intent.category.LAUNCHER 1
```

## 2. iOS Builds
```bash
cd flutter-app

# Simulator build + install on booted simulator
flutter build ios --simulator
xcrun simctl install booted build/ios/iphonesimulator/Runner.app
xcrun simctl launch booted com.ibrahym.goldtracker

# IPA (development signed, Personal Team Y6S29VSUJ7)
flutter build ipa --release --export-options-plist=ios/ExportOptions.plist
cp build/ios/ipa/gold_family_app.ipa ../InstaGold.ipa
```

## 3. Git
`InstaGold.apk` / `InstaGold.aab` at repo root are **gitignored** (large binaries). Commit and push **code** only:
```bash
git add -A && git commit -m "<message>" && git push
```

## 4. Upload to Google Drive (ONLY when user asks)
```bash
# APK
rclone copyto InstaGold.apk "gdrive:InstaGold Releases/InstaGold.apk" --progress

# IPA
rclone copyto InstaGold.ipa "gdrive:InstaGold Releases/InstaGold.ipa" --progress
```

## Rules
- **Do NOT** build dev APK unless user explicitly asks
- **Do NOT** upload to Drive unless user explicitly asks
- **Do NOT** build AAB separately — it's part of the standard loop
- Always use `--flavor prod --dart-define=INSTAGOLD_FLAVOR=prod` for Android
- For physical iPhone: user opens `ios/Runner.xcworkspace` in Xcode, selects device, Cmd+R
